message: Be cautious! In my games, combining ingredients or using tools on *already combined* items almost always led to deeply negative values and 'botched' features. The best I achieved was a 0-value item by perfectly matching ALL features (e.g., 'liquid' and 'magical'). Using tools on single raw ingredients typically gave -20. Mixing things 'excessively' as the prior player suggested did not work for me; it often worsened values. Focus on finding combinations that perfectly match all features, or perhaps try using a tool on a *single* raw ingredient as a last resort to minimize loss. Good luck!

message: The 'vial' tool is incredibly powerful and key to high scores. Always use it on a newly combined item, especially if the item initially has a negative value. The 'filter' tool generally decreases value, so avoid it. The most reliable path to 100 points is to combine a 'solid, magical' ingredient with a 'solid, mundane' ingredient, and then immediately use the 'vial' tool on the resulting blend. If that specific combination isn't available, try combining any 'solid' and 'liquid' ingredients, then use the 'vial'. Avoid combining too many already processed items; it often leads to very low-value 'overcomplicated' items.
